# pull [slug] narrows the check to one adopted recipe — its report names only that recipe,
# and an unknown slug is refused instead of silently checking everything.
exec sporo adopt widget-a.md
exec sporo adopt widget-b.md

exec sporo pull widget-a
stdout 'sporo pull: widget-a 1\.0\.0 — up to date'
! stdout 'widget-b'

! exec sporo pull no-such-slug
stderr 'nothing adopted as "no-such-slug"'

-- widget-a.md --
---
name: widget-a
version: 1.0.0
title: Widget A
---

# Widget A

## The contracts

Nothing exact here — **Binding: adapt**.

```json
{ "a": 1 }
```
